- VSCode Version: 1.5.0

The check if the globally installed tsc version matches the TS version has a "Don't check again' message box. If pressed we never check again, even if the user opens another workspace. The reason why I did this is that the tsc is global. Now that I think about it again I am wondering if we should check once per workspace. 

@waderyan @egamma opinions?

Our type definitions for `Promise.is` and `Promise.as` are wrong because the implementation only checks for arguments being a `thenable` meaning they don't necessarily return winjs-promises. 

```
public static as<ValueType>(value:ValueType):TPromise<ValueType>;
```

should be 

```
public static as<ValueType>(value: Thenable<ValueType>): Thenable<ValueType>;
public static as<ValueType>(value: TPromise<ValueType>): TPromise<ValueType>;
public static as<ValueType>(value: ValueType): TPromise<ValueType>;
```

![screen shot 2016-09-09 at 14 29 49](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1794099/18388027/219d3abc-76a0-11e6-9ea2-66dbd8997ba0.png)

The method that does what you would expect is `TPromise#wrap`.
